[3]
Date: Fri 27 Sep 2002
From:ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Direction de la sante publique de Montreal-Centre, Fri 27 Sep 2002
[edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/wnv-vwn/index.html>

Quebec: First Human Case Confirmed
----------------------------------
The following are the West Nile virus surveillance results as of Fri 27 Sep
2002.
Birds:
A total of 115 West Nile virus infected birds reported from
Montreal-Centre, Laurentides, Outaouais, Mauricie et Centre-du-Quebec,
Monteregie, Laval, Estrie, Chaudiere-Appalanches, Lanaudiere, and Quebec.
Mosquitoes:
A total of 25 pools of mosquitoes has tested West Nile virus-positive. The
pools originated from Laurentides, Monteregie, Montreal-Centre, Laval, and
Mauricie et Centre-du-Quebec.
Humans:
A total of 4 cases of human West Nile virus infection has been reported; 1
confirmed case in Laurentides and 3 probable cases in Montreal-Centre.
--
